cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is about attacking deep learning based computer vision algorithms, specifically object detectors and instance segmentation algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel loss function and uses iterative optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with adversarial attacks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves optimization and loss functions, which could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
